				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "B7lJx591RuuxmLLt5uliJQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "What is the design of the current player system?"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-12T20:54:58.284783-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-15T18:01:09.307196-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "CDYNO7FsR9et/QTs/V6t0w=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "{{gtClass:RlAbstractMediaPlayer}} provides the basic API. Concrete implementations: {{gtClass:RlMediaPlayer}} and {{gtClass:LlPlaylistPlayer}}.\n- Responsibilities: play media, which includes common actions like play, pause, skip; can be multiple instances on one source\n- Collaborators: \n  - `container`:  precisely defined place that the media is playing e.g. a webPage in a browser, an MPV instance\n    - currently the player is actually not collaborating with the container, just passing it to `playable`.  **This is a possible simplification point - maybe store the playable**\n    - Examples are {{gtClass:RlAppleScriptWebPage}}, {{gtClass:RlPythonMpv}} (also a driver)\n  - `driver`: Primary responsibility is to `#show:` the player and return a `container`. Can serve as the container if no finer grained specificity is required (e.g. which page in a browser? which tab in an application?)\n    - There is no common base class (a problem?). \n    - Examples are {{gtClass:RlPythonMpv}}, {{gtClass:RlApplescriptMediaDriver}}, {{gtClass:RlMacPreviewDriver}}.\n  - `playable`:\n    - determined from the `source`\n    - an element in the container\n    - Collaborates with `container`\n    - Examples are {{gtClass:RlDomVideo}}, {{gtClass:RlDomYouTubeVideo}}, {{gtClass:RlContainedMedia}}\n  - `source`: what we are playing\n    - typically a resource or library item\n    - Responsibilities:\n      - answer questions which are static (ie independent of player state) in nature (e.g. duration), but not directly playable\n      - provide a `container`, `driver` and `playable`, or information to create one "
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-15T17:49:51.351709-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-06-15T18:03:16.903535-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "hxreNvbSTySI68pyd/7plw=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "How much can we distill the above? \n\nPlayer seems simple enough - a single object for users to interact with that hides all the complexity underneath.\n\nPlayable: seems essential\n- Previously, we were putting playing API in the `source`s themselves, taking the container as an argument. This is not generally workable because a source might be playable in multiple types of containers e.g. a video can be played in a web browser, VLC, IINA, Quicktime, etc.\n- For the same video source above, mught be a {{gtClass:RlDomVideo}}, or (hypothetical) `RlQuickTimeDocument`\n\nContainer: this seems essential as well because this "
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
